  "strategy": [
    "Alternate between short forward moves and scanning rotations to maximize marker detection.",
    "Commit to actions (forward or rotation) until a significant event (obstacle, marker_seen, marker_lost) occurs.",
    "Prioritize move_to_marker as soon as marker_seen is detected.",
    "When marker_close is detected, stop to avoid collision and complete the task.",
    "After obstacle detection, perform recovery (backward or rotate) and then scan before resuming forward movement.",
    "Avoid oscillations by only allowing one rotation direction per state.",
    "Insert explicit scan states after forward or recovery actions to prevent long straight runs.",
    "Return to exploration (scan) if the marker is lost.",
    "Never allow move_forward in response to obstacle_front; always recover first.",
    "Do not allow stop solely due to marker_seen; only stop when marker_close is active."
  ]
